text: Nadezhda Smirnova (Russian: Надежда Смирнова; born on 22 February 1996 in Sergiyev Posad) is a Russian professional football player who currently plays for CSKA Moscow and the Russian national team. She played for Russia in the UEFA Women's Euro 2017. She has also played for Rossiyanka, and Zorky Krasnogorsk. == References == == Other websites == * Nadezhda Smirnova at UEFA * Nadezhda Smirnova at Soccerway Category:Russian footballers Category:1996 births Category:Living people
